{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "18", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "04", "M": "36", "S": "28"}}, "news": [{"title": "Bharat Future City draws 90 real estate proposals, approvals crawl amid delays", "para": "Real estate developers are cautiously investing in Bharat Future City's development. Most investment activity is concentrated along specific highways, and many await a clearer roadmap. The Future City Development Authority has received numerous applications, but only a few have secured approvals. Developers are adopting a wait-and-watch approach until the master plan is ready. Staff shortages at the FCDA are reportedly causing delays in processing applications.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/bharat-future-city-project-90-real-estate-proposals-amidst-approval-delays/132473813?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1494937/132473813.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Volvo Group leases six lakh sq ft office space in Bengaluru", "para": "India's office market recorded its strongest-ever quarter in Q2 2026, with gross leasing reaching a record 24.6 million sq ft, according to CBRE. Volvo Group signed one of the quarter's largest deals, leasing 600,000 sq ft in Bengaluru, as GCCs, flexible workspaces and technology firms continued to drive demand despite geopolitical uncertainty.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/commercial/volvo-group-leases-six-lakh-sq-ft-office-space-in-bengaluru/132473639?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-31328/132473639.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "commercial"}, {"title": "Rooms in stilt parking razed, guesthouses sealed in Gurugram DLF-3", "para": "Gurugram authorities demolished illegal structures in stilt parking areas.  Four properties were sealed for unauthorized commercial activities in residential buildings.  Encroachments were cleared from approximately 4.5 kilometers of public right of way.  This enforcement drive followed previous actions and complied with court directives.  The campaign will now proceed to DLF-4 for further action.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/rooms-in-stilt-parking-razed-guesthouses-sealed-in-gurugram-dlf-3/132473599?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1988061/132473599.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}]}